text.tspan: Infant mortality vs. prevalence of prenatal care, 2021
Infant mortality is defined as the share of newborns who die in the first year of life. This is measured against the
share of pregnant women who receive prenatal care.
Data source: UN Inter-agency Group for Child Mortality Estimation (via World Bank); Demographic and Health Surveys (DHS) and
